Question: What do you consider to be a healthy relationship?
Answer:
One where there is a good ratio for positive and negative feedback, as in, at least 5 to 1 (feedback might not be the word, I'm talking pretty general like saying positive things and actions that portray such). This is not usually something you have to worry about for budding relationships, more so after being together for a year or two.
  
  One where there is little manipulation, especially concious manipulation, and none or almost no malicious or selfish manipulation.
  
  One where there is no abuse. Abuse refers to a pattern, I don't strictly mean physical abuse either.
  
  One where each party wishes the best for the other(s) even if it might mean the relationship ending, at least after thinking on it for long enough.
  
  One where each party can have friends of any gender and hang out with them without stressing any other party out. Not saying jealousy is shameful, just that it is something you can't let take over you or your relationships. It's also important to trust partners.
  
  Assuming a traditional monogamous or non-open poly relationship: one where parties don't seek romantic/sexual intimacy with those that are not their partners.

Question: Does one of your senses provide a more "real" experience for you, than the others, which and why? :)
Answer:
Maybe sight, because I love aesthetics, colors, patterns, and to create such things. Also because my hearing isn't what it used to be, I would rate hearing as my number two, especially with music and other pleasant or enjoyable sounds, taste is somewhere after and smell might be in last place (it is also my worst sense as far as I know.
  
  I'm not sure where I would put touch, I know it increases the release of oxytocin and prolongs life as well as functioning life. Well, when between humans anyway, or other similar beings. Then there's also that I would rate touch as my number one love language or at least at the top. However, it doesn't do anything for me artistically or creatively. It could inspire creativity, but it's not as much an expression of creativity I mean (not that it isn't or can't be, just not to as high an extent for me). I know it would be above smell for sure, i'd say above taste as well. When it comes to auditory and visual stimulus nothing can top the visual part. I might tie it with the sense of hearing or put it a bit above it. Yes, I can still imagine sounds and sights after losing those senses, but imagining isn't the same because you will never hear or see anything new and you'll forget details of things you have seen and heard as time goes by at least for most things. Plus for sight it would mean I couldn't really draw or design visuals and create digital art anymore, not in the way I enjoy doing such things anyway. It would also make a lot of things impossible that I enjoy doing as well, not just robbing my of aesthetics and things I would enjoy seeing alone.
  
  I'd say the sense of touch provides the realest experience to me, I don't know how to express why that is the case at least not yet, I've never thought about it. Part of it is that I don't really experience touch in dreams, not like I do with the other senses.

Question: How far would you go for the one you love?
Answer:
Further than I probably should as long as I can deduce that it is mutual. I feel as if the me in love and the me not in love are two very different people and they can both observe themselves and the other self. It's strange. A lot of my views, ideas, and desires change. In terms of ideas/views I try to be more consistent, also, how they change hasn't changed based on who the target is either. So I'm not saying I adopt the targets views.
  
  I would also say the me in love is more bold or passionate in terms of expression through art for the most part. Sort of like having a muse.
  
  Maybe you could argue that the me in love is just more honest/emotional and less pragmatic/logical. Some of it is also just biological. Like how I will change my mind on kids for instance. Where when I'm not in love I think about it logically, but also less passionately. I think about how I wouldn't want kids until I'm in an optimal place financially and once I learn a lot about raising children, child psychology, and have a good mindset going into it so that it is my best effort. There have also been times where I've thought getting a vasectomy to prevent the in love me from doing anything stupid in the future. I also feel that having kids shouldn't be as easy as it is biologically when it is a huge responsibility and that the process of adoption is closer to how it should be. I know there isn't exactly equal treatment with the adoption process in the US, but it's much closer to an ideal system than sex which is pleasurable and easy (between heterosexual or bisexual individuals of of the opposite sex).

Question: Do you often suffer from sleeplessness?
Would you rather have a rewind button or a pause button in your life?
Answer:
If the pause button is unlimited in how msny times I get to pause and for how long and the rewind button is unlimited in how many times I can use it I would choose the rewind button. I'll assume there is no consequence to either and that I retain my prior memories when rewinding (not perfectly like all memory) because otherwise it's useless.
  
  I could go mad either way. If I wanted time to think, either would work (could keep going back to think). If I wanted to prolong living or live forever, either would work. If I wanted to live forever in ongoing time, one would work, if I wanted to undo/redo only one would work.
  
  Rewind is easily superior. There is nothing you can do with pausing that you can't do with rewinding given "time".

Question: Which word do you 🙃😗😧👩👦want everyone to stop using?
Answer: Irregardless! Nonsensical and redundant word. Why did they add it to the dictionary? Why?! Both the prefix and suffix do the same thing. Regard and regardless covers all bases, there's even disregard. Besides, without without regard being a double negative means it should be positive, double negative, negative negates negative. So irregardless means regard, not regardless. When you say irregardless, you are saying with regard to whatever it may be (not without regard to it). I might say it as a joke or as satire now and then, but never seriously.

Question: How can you tell you are being manipulated?
Answer:
It's hard at first but once you know the signs it's pretty easy to tell. You first have to understand what manipulation looks like which is: Someone who is emotionally manipulating you may do so in subtle ways, like judging and criticizing your actions. They might make a mean comment about your choice of friends, for example. Another sign of emotional manipulation is trying to create feelings of embarrassment or guilt. There's Psychological manipulation too that you can look up.
  
  Here are some ways: You feel fear, obligation and guilt. You’re questioning yourself (aka they're gaslighting you). There are strings attached (If you don’t meet the manipulator’s expectation, you will be made out to be ungrateful). You notice the ‘foot-in-the-door’ and ‘door-in-the-face’ techniques. Plain Old Bullying. They pull the "If You Really Loved Me..." Emotional Blackmail. Playing The Victim (THIS IS A HUGE ONE). Gaslighting (ANOTHER BIG ONE). Convenient Neediness, they're always "joking".
  
  What to do if you think you’re being manipulated? Talk to a therapist or call the National Domestic Violence Hotline as they know what to do. Try not to let the manipulators behavior affect you personally. I know that's easier said then done but it's really important to not let them get to you.
  
  Some more: Stubborn Headedness, Knowing Your Weaknesses, Creating Confusion, & Being Passive-Aggressive. Most of the manipulators are pathological liars. Psychological manipulators are often what they call emotional vampires or parasites. That means that they will make you feel bad whenever they feel bad, or make you feel guilty because they feel bad. They pressure you. Manipulators will often yell or put you in an uncomfortable situation because of their behavior. (Stone cold/letting you take the initiative) Manipulators will let you speak first because this allows them to get to know your opinions, emotions or even weak spots.

Allow yourself time to heal and do not get upset with yourself. PUT YOURSELF FIRST! Make sure the people you are surrounding yourself with care about you and are people you can count on. Sometimes the one hurting has to speak first. Let others know how you're feeling in the best way you can possibly describe it. Get out of the house when you're feeling depressed; it's ok if when you're out and about that you still don't feel the greatest. It's not always about feeling good while doing things, allowing yourself to be surround by positive does better your feelings over time. Challenge your negative thoughts. Tell them no because they're lying to you. Every negative thing you've ever felt; is a lie. Daily affirmations are helpful.

How to increase self-esteem?
Answer:
Sometimes learning where the lack of it comes from is helpful because then you can start doing things that will improve it.
  
  -Focus on the positive things in life.
  
  -Avoid 'should' and 'must' statements. If you find that your thoughts are full of these words, you might be putting unreasonable demands on yourself — or on others. Removing these words from your thoughts can lead to more realistic expectations.
  
  - Remind yourself that nobody is perfect and we all make mistakes. That's how we learn.
  
  -GET MOVIN!
  
  -Do what makes YOU happy.
  
  -Celebrate the small stuff because they're important.
  
  -Do something creative.
  
  -Get clear on your values.
  
  -Heal your past.
  
  -It's very important to stop worrying about what others think and to stop yourself from overthinking.

Question: What do men really want in a relationship?
Answer:
Every guy is different and I can only speak for myself.
  
  What I want, is emotional intimacy, respect, some praise here and there and acceptance. A physical connection, some romance, security, emotional maturity, communication, partnership, some fun, and some space when needed. A connection, someone who is patient, someone who isn't afraid to be different and doesn't want to fit in with the rest of the world. I like independent woman, one who is honest and caring. A woman who knows how to compliment me on my personality and not just my looks. It makes me feel better about myself when one does so. Don't be afraid to be the boss and have your way with me. 8 Life Lessons
Answer:
1. Let go of anger. When we erupt in anger we often feel much worse. Hence, it’s better to cool off and to work on staying calm.
  
  2. When people treat you badly it’s rarely about you. More often it tells you how that person is feeling, or some other issues that are bothering them.
  
  3. You’re not the only one who has struggled with this issue – so don’t feel so awful, or put yourself down.
  
  4. Enjoy the good times, and savour every moment as life is a precious gift to be enjoyed.
  
  5. Work and be persistent as it’s worth the slog and pain. In the end it makes a difference as the pay off is success.
  
  6. You need to find a passion and set yourself some goals if you want to go somewhere, and makes something of life.
  
  7. Relationships can teach us so much about ourselves. Both the good and the bad can show us who we really are. They reveal what we think, and how we feel, about ourselves – as well as what our values and our expectations are.
  
  8. Don’t put off to tomorrow what you could do today. You’ll achieve so much more if you push full steam ahead. And easing off too much sows the seeds of laziness. You’ll have much more self respect if you achieve more than you’d planned.

Answer: When you've suffered with mental health for so long and am use those extreme highs and lows, it can feel extremely weird when you're finally stable enough to live your life and enjoy it. I don't remember the last time I was mentally stable and now that I am, it's been quite a journey. I have to retrain my brain of my own thoughts and emotions. Make myself realize that what I am feeling now is completely normal and not to become suddenly overwhelmed by not knowing if what I am feeling is normal or not. I am self-aware nowadays which is a good thing but I find myself filled with a lot of questions and trying to sort out my emotions and thoughts. To realize that a bad day is just a bad day nowadays and it's okay to not be okay for a day or two is still a struggle I have. Especially when I feel depressed. It scares me the most along side with my anxiety. Yesterday I had a day full of meetings, after my meetings, I had therapy. On my way to therapy I was anxious and shaking. It was my abusers birthday and a lot of others things were going on previously and I almost got hit by a semi. Once I arrived at the clinic, checked myself in and checked myself in again and got my clip board, I could barely even rate my emotions because my hands where shaking so much. It took me 15 mins of my session to finally chill out. Relaxing and using breathing techniques are one of my BIGGEST struggle.
